            android:layout_margin="10dp"
            app:cardCornerRadius="0dp"
            app:cardElevation="6dp"
            app:cardUseCompatPadding="true">

            <LinearLayout
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:orientation="vertical"
                android:padding="5dp">

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:textSize="20sp"
                    android:text="Paper Title: An Android-based End-To-End System to Recognize Tea Leaf Diseases"
                    android:textStyle="bold" />

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_marginTop="6dp"
                    android:textSize="16sp"
                    android:justificationMode="inter_word"
                    android:padding="2dp"
                    android:text="Short Abstract: Tea, a major plantation crop in Bangladesh, is severely impacted by various leaf diseases, particularly in remote areas where professional diagnosis is challenging. To address this, we introduce a new high-resolution dataset of tea leaf images collected from Moulvi Bazar, Sylhet, Bangladesh. This dataset is categorized into four classes: healthy, tea leaf blight, tea red leaf spot, and tea red scab. We propose F-TeaNet, a novel model combining Fourier Neural Network and transformer architecture for accurate disease detection.This model is utilized as the foundation for a smartphone application that does real-time, automated disease recognition from captured and uploaded images and shows the confidence scores. Early and precise recognition facilitates targeted interventions, such as selective pesticide application, promoting sustainable agricultural practices, improving crop yield, and reducing reliance on broad-spectrum chemical treatments." />
            </LinearLayout>
        </com.google.android.material.card.MaterialCardView>

